<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08969</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT ESTABLISHING THE NATIONAL ROADS AND RAILWAYS SAFETY BOARD, PROVIDING FOR ITS POWERS AND COMPOSITION, APPROPRIATIONS, AND FOR OTHER PURPOSES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Proposes that road and rail safety regulation of all land vehicles, including public utility vehicles, should be with a National Land Transportation Safety Board, not with the LTFRB or LTO.

Seeks to authorize the RRSB to set standards on road-worthiness of land vehicles, cancel 
or suspend driver's licenses, investigate road accidents and resolve administrative cases arising from road mishaps.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ABAYON, HARLIN NEIL III J.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-01-31</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON GOVERNMENT ENTERPRISES AND PRIVATIZATION ON 2019-02-04</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SECONDARILY REFERRED TO THE COMMITTEE(S) ON TRANSPORTATION</td></tr></table>